properties.text: Using this book is simple and little interactive. In the next few pages you will find list of ores (Small Ores and Ore Veins). You can click on the ore you are looking for and it will take you to propper page. The page will list information about the ore. Height is in what Y level can the ore spawn. Mining Tool Level means the required level of your pickaxe to be able to mine that ore. And Dimensions lists where the ore can spawn.

On the Ore Veins pages there is one extra info and these are Layers. Primary, Secondary, Inbetween and Around. The upper 2-4 levels of a vein will be almost all 'Primary' ore, the lower 2-4 levels will be almost all 'Secondary' ore, and the middle 2-4 levels will be mostly 'Inbetween' ore. 'Around' ore appears randomly interspersed throughout the vein. In total, a vein will contain roughly equal portions of Primary and Secondary ore, slightly less Inbetween ore, and notably less Around ore.
